      <h2>4. The Bug Hunt: A Three-Layer Onion</h2>

      <p>
        The talk included a classic debugging story. One day, the session broke with: <code>tool_use.input: Field required</code>.
      </p>

      <p>
        Root cause? A three-layer onion:
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Layer 1:</strong> Gemini CLI returned <code>undefined</code> for zero-argument tools.</li>
        <li><strong>Layer 2:</strong> This corrupted entry got written to the session JSONL file (permanent damage).</li>
        <li><strong>Layer 3:</strong> Anthropic's API rejected the undefined input, breaking everything.</li>
      </ol>

      <p>
        The fix? One line of code: <code>arguments: toolCall.input ?? {}</code>
      </p>
      <p>
        The entire investigation ‚Äî searching GitHub issues, reading source code, manually patching files on the VM ‚Äî was done by Claude Code.
      </p>

